  "title": "docs(cloudinary): Use https cloudinary link to avoid mixed-content",
  "body": "Here is what I currently see online:\r\n![image](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/283419/26737293/be73c69e-47c9-11e7-894f-2e8352704dab.png)\r\n\r\nThis is because we load the React logo through Cloudinary on an `http` request while the website is in `https`:\r\n![image](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/283419/26737309/d6123538-47c9-11e7-928b-deae031b2716.png)\r\n\r\nSimple fix, but better result:\r\n![image](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/283419/26737323/dffbc686-47c9-11e7-8481-1d96828bae0a.png)\r\n",
